name: Framed Street Irregulars — 005
description:
005 is a new drop in the series in which I will add generated sounds alongside with random changes on the algorithm and process to generate the piece. It will be a transition of the series from a silent frame of images to a nostalgic video, with a generative sound, that will give you an experience to watch an image like you're traveling to a memory from the past.

The base of the sound that you hear from this piece was made using a tool created by an artist and programmer, Olivia Jack. The tool analyses the image information to which then translates it to various note that creates the sound. Then I used the generated sound as the base and added few effects such as reverb.

"Framed Street Irregulars" is an experimental series by LEMSSS in which he uses algorithms and javascript code techniques to display his Black & White Street Photographs into a generative 1:1 video style of stills.

----

— Resolution 1500x1500
— Format MP4
— Images made with P5js and Native Javascript 
— Base sound made with PIXELSYNTH (Olivia Jack)
— Duration: 60 seconds
